article.headline: Stony Brook 34, Cent. Connecticut St. 7
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Brandon Mason scored three touchdowns to lead Stony Brook to a 34-7 victory over Central Connecticut on Saturday. Mason caught an 8-yard TD pass from Josh Dudash and had identical 2-yard touchdown runs for the Seawolves (5-4). He ran for 138 yards on 24 carries and had two receptions for another 22. Dudash was 14-for-22 for 232 yards and three touchdowns, including a 37-yarder by Dwayne Eley. Jo Jo Freeman scored on a 1-yard run at 3:43 of the first quarter for the Blue Devils (6-4).
